《'''每日野獸'''》（{{lang-en|'''''The Daily Beast'''''}}），又譯為《'''野兽日报'''》，是一家[[美國|美國]]新聞網站，2008年10月6日上線，由[[IAC/InterActiveCorp|IAC/InterActiveCorp]]持有。2014年月瀏覽量達1700萬。<ref name="Capital New York">{{cite news|url=http://www.capitalnewyork.com/article/media/2014/06/8546580/leadership-changes-daily-beast|title=Leadership changes at The Daily Beast|work=Capital|accessdate=4 June 2014|first=Joe|last=Pompeo|date=4 June 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150417035219/http://www.capitalnewyork.com/article/media/2014/06/8546580/leadership-changes-daily-beast|archive-date=2015-04-17|dead-url=yes}}</ref>

==歷史==
《每日野獸》在2008年10月6日上線，屬[[IAC/InterActiveCorp|IAC/InterActiveCorp]]旗下。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.thewrap.com/daily-beast-hires-executive-editor-fill-role-vacated-tina-brown |title=Daily Beast Hires Executive Editor; Promotes John Avlon to Editor-In-Chief (Updated) |publisher=The Wrap |access-date=2015-04-11 |archive-date=2021-04-07 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210407194549/https://www.thewrap.com/daily-beast-hires-executive-editor-fill-role-vacated-tina-brown/ |dead-url=no }}</ref> 其名來自[[伊夫林·沃|伊夫林·沃]]1938年出版的[[小說|小說]]《[[獨家新聞_(小說)|獨家新聞]]》（Scoop）中的一份虛構[[報紙|報紙]]。<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.ft.com/cms/s/0/0a157900-9304-11dd-98b5-0000779fd18c.html#axzz1QveyEsa1|title=Another scoop for Tina Brown as she swaps print for web|newspaper=Financial Times|location=London|author=Edgecliffe-Johnson, Andrew|date=5 October 2008|accessdate=2015-04-11|archive-date=2016-03-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160320234820/http://www.ft.com/cms/s/0/0a157900-9304-11dd-98b5-0000779fd18c.html#axzz1QveyEsa1|dead-url=no}}{{subscription required}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2008/10/06/the-daily-beast-tina-brow_n_132150.html|newspaper=The Huffington Post|agency=''[[Financial_Times|Financial Times]]''|title=The Daily Beast: Tina Brown Launches Much-Awaited News Site|date=6 October 2008|accessdate=2015-04-11|archive-date=2008-10-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081008185032/http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2008/10/06/the-daily-beast-tina-brow_n_132150.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Moss|first=Stephen|title=William Boot: Evelyn Waugh's legendary journalist|url=http://www.guardian.co.uk/books/2010/jun/01/william-boot-evelyn-waugh|accessdate=4 April 2013|newspaper=The Guardian|quote=What is interesting about Brown's view is that while most readers see the Beast as monstrous, she admires its energy. 'That newspaper just seemed to me to represent British popular journalism at its most antic,' she says. 'That's what I love about it. It has energy and a slightly irresponsible feel. I don't see it as negative. There is something very joyful about it.'|date=1 June 2010|archive-date=2012-11-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121107153528/http://www.guardian.co.uk/books/2010/jun/01/william-boot-evelyn-waugh|dead-url=no}}</ref>

2010年11月12日，《每日野獸》和《[[新聞週刊|新聞週刊]]》宣佈合併，形成新聞週刊每日野獸公司（The Newsweek Daily Beast Company）。2013年8月3日，IAC將《新聞週刊》賣給《[[国际财经时报|国际财经时报]]》 的母公司IBT Media。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://nymag.com/daily/intelligencer/2013/08/iac-found-someone-to-buy-newsweek.html|title=New York, "IAC Found Someone to Buy Zombie Newsweek," 3 August 2013.|work=Daily Intelligencer|access-date=2015-04-11|archive-date=2018-09-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180918110424/http://nymag.com/daily/intelligencer/2013/08/iac-found-someone-to-buy-newsweek.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>

